headline: Why Fidelity National Financial, Kimberly-Clark, And Black Hills Are Winners For Passive Income
summary: Companies with a long history of paying dividends and consistently hiking them remain appealing to income-focused investors. Fidelity National Financial, Kimberly-Clark, and Black Hills have rewarded shareholders for years and recently announced dividend increases. These companies currently offer dividend yields of around 3% to 4%.
